      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"it depends\" thing but that feels kinda vague for a paper. if you had to pick one side for the sake of an argument, which one is more supported by current evidence? like, is the \"dangerous\" side actually more scientifically backed than the \"cohesion\" side? just trying to see if there's a dominant view in academia right now.",
